## Troubleshooting

| Symptom | Likely cause | Fix |
|---------|--------------|-----|
| Next ID ~600001+ | Imported **ordered** SQL with MOSC block | Expected after sync; use **renumbered** import if you want lower IDs |
| Duplicate PK on create | Table sequence behind `MAX(id)` | Run `sync_all_table_sequences.sql`; call `POST /api/admin/sync-sequence` |
| Executive id jumps to 800+ | Old shared `sequence_generator` still in use | Schema rebuild + per-table migration |
| Batch job duplicate PK | Spring Batch sequences stale | Run `sync_spring_batch_sequences.sql` |
| Import OK, app still wrong on **other machine** | Sync scripts not run on that DB | Run Steps 7 + 7b on **each** database that received INSERTs |
| Renumber FK warnings | Old script / wrong import file | Re-run latest `renumber_sql_insert_ids.cjs`; check `id-mapping-report.json` `fkWarningCount: 0` |

